Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the BOOKReader web project.

## What was implemented:

1. **Fetched Latest Documentation**: Retrieved the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart to ensure the most up-to-date installation instructions were followed.

2. **Installed @vercel/analytics Package**: Added @vercel/analytics version 2.0.1 to the project dependencies using npm. The package was installed in the web directory where the React + Vite application resides.

3. **Configured Analytics Component**: Integrated the Analytics component into the application following the official React-specific instructions:
   - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
   - Added the `<Analytics />` component to the root App component in `src/App.tsx`
   - Placed it at the end of the app div to ensure proper tracking across all routes

## Files Modified:

- **web/package.json**: Added @vercel/analytics to dependencies
- **web/package-lock.json**: Updated with new dependency tree (448 packages added)
- **web/src/App.tsx**: Added Analytics import and component

## Framework Details:

This project uses:
- React 19.0.0
- Vite 6.0.5 (build tool)
- React Router DOM for routing
- TypeScript for type safety

The Analytics component was added to the main App component, which wraps all routes, ensuring analytics tracking is active across the entire application including the Library, AddContent, Reader, Recap, Review, and Settings pages.

## Verification:

- ✅ TypeScript type checking passed (`npm run typecheck`)
- ✅ Production build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
- ✅ No linting errors introduced
- ✅ All dependencies properly resolved

## Next Steps:

To complete the setup on Vercel:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
3. Verify the analytics are working by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*` after deployment

The Analytics component will automatically begin tracking page views and web vitals once deployed to Vercel with analytics enabled in the dashboard.
